<refentry id="MONITOR-ALTERJOB">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>ALTER JOB</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>7</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo>Manage - Language Statements</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>ALTER JOB</refname>
    <refpurpose>alter one row job information in the job table. The column of "interval" requires an integer value, unit is "second"; The input string of "command" column should be in single quote. If using user-defined monitor item, the input of sql string format likes 'insert into tb_name select adbmonitor_job(''host_name'', ''item_name'')', the item_name in job item table\n\n
    the common used functions for monitor are:\n
    for tps qps 'select monitor_databasetps_insert_data()'\n    
    for database summary 'select monitor_databaseitem_insert_data()'\n  
    for host 'select  monitor_get_hostinfo()'\n 
    for slow log 'select monitor_slowlog_insert_data()'\n   
    for gtm handle 'select monitor_handle_gtm(\n
        \tname 'nodename' default '''',\n
        \tbool bforce default true,\n 
        \tint reconnect_attempts default 3,\n 
        \tint reconnect_interval default 2,\n 
        \tint select_timeout default 15)'\n 
    for coordinator handle 'select monitor_handle_coordinator()'\n
    for datanode handle 'select monitor_handle_datanode(\n 
        \tname 'nodename' default '''',\n 
        \tbool bforce default true,\n 
        \tint reconnect_attempts default 3,\n 
        \tint reconnect_interval default 2,\n 
        \tint select_timeout default 15)\n\n

      the limit of monitor_handle_gtm and monitor_handle_datanode functions:\n
      2<=reconnect_attempts<=60, 2<=reconnect_interval<120, 2<=select_timeout<120\n
      reconnect_interval and select_timeout unit: "second". </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <indexterm zone="monitor-addjob">
    <primary>ALTER JOB</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis>
ALTER JOB <replaceable class="parameter">job_name</replaceable> ( <replaceable class="parameter">option</replaceable> )
ALTER JOB ALL ( <replaceable class="parameter">option</replaceable> )

<phrase>where <replaceable class="parameter">option</replaceable> can be the following:</phrase>
("ALTER JOB ALL" not support modify the column of "command" and "desc")

    NEXTTIME = <replaceable class="parameter">next_time</replaceable>,
    INTERVAL = <replaceable class="parameter">interval</replaceable>,
    STATUS = <replaceable class="parameter">status</replaceable>,
    COMMAND = <replaceable class="parameter">sql_string</replaceable>,
    DESC = <replaceable class="parameter">description</replaceable></synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>
<command>ALTER JOB</command> alter one row job information in the job table.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">job_name</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
    Job name.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">next_time</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
    The next time the job runs.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">interval</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
    Interval time, unit is seconds.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">status</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
    The flag shows whether the job needs to run.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">sql_string</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
    The format is standard SQL. If we want to execute arm batch on given server machine, the format input string likes 'INSERT INTO table_name SELECT ADBMONITOR_JOB(''host_name'', ''item_name'')', the input string of "command" column should be in single quote.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">description</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
    Description of the job.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>


  <refsect1>
    <title>Examples</title>

    <para>
Alter job1's interval time in job table:
      <programlisting>
ALTER JOB job1 (INTERVAL = 60);
</programlisting>
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>See Also</title>

    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member><xref linkend="monitor-addjob"></member>
    </simplelist>
  </refsect1>


</refentry>
